headlines.description: — Lamar Jackson hurt an ankle and lost one of his top targets to a more severe injury.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ravens handle Bengals 34-20 after Joe Burrow exits in the 2nd quarter with a wrist injury

headlines.description: — As Dorian Thompson-Robinson sat in the back of a golf cart swiping through text messages overwhelming his phone, wide receiver Elijah Moore slid in to an empty seat behind Cleveland’s rookie quarterback.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rookie QB Dorian Thompson-Robinson rallies Browns to a last-second 13-10 win over Steelers

headlines.description: — Jared Goff was having perhaps his worst game in three years with the Detroit Lions — whose fans even booed him at times — until it was time to win.
headlines.shortLinkText: NFC North-leading Lions rally from 12-point deficit late to beat Bears 31-26 on Montgomery's TD run

events.name: Los Angeles Chargers at Green Bay Packers

headlines.description: — With Green Bay down to one healthy running back, Jordan Love realized the Packers' hopes likely rested on his right arm.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jordan Love's late TD pass lifts Packers to 23-20 victory over Chargers

events.name: Las Vegas Raiders at Miami Dolphins

headlines.description: — Jalen Ramsey had his Miami teammates — even highlight-machine Tyreek Hill — in awe with his game-sealing interception Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Ramsey makes game-sealing interception, Dolphins overcome 3 turnovers to beat Raiders 20-13

events.name: New York Giants at Washington Commanders

headlines.description: — Ron Rivera walked back into the locker room, saw Sam Howell sitting at his locker with his head down and asked the young quarterback, “You all right?”
headlines.shortLinkText: Howell has 3 interceptions among 6 Commanders turnovers in their 31-19 loss to the last-place Giants

headlines.description: — Dak Prescott felt the main goal coming into Sunday's game was not to overlook the NFL's worst team.
headlines.shortLinkText: Prescott throws 2 TDs, Bland ties NFL record with 4th pick-6 in Cowboys' 33-10 rout of Panthers

headlines.description: — Trevor Lawrence insisted all week that he had no concerns about Jacksonville's sluggish offense.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jaguars bounce back from embarrassing loss with 34-14 drubbing of AFC South rival Titans

headlines.description: — C.J. Stroud was asked if he'd think twice about making certain throws after he was intercepted a season-high three times in Houston's win over Arizona.
headlines.shortLinkText: C.J. Stroud leads Texans to 21-16 win over Cardinals despite throwing season-high 3 interceptions

events.name: Tampa Bay Buccaneers at San Francisco 49ers

headlines.description: — Brock Purdy felt it was important for the San Francisco 49ers to get back to an attacking mindset following a three-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Perfect Brock Purdy throws 3 TD passes to lead the 49ers past the Bucs 27-14

events.name: New York Jets at Buffalo Bills

headlines.description: — Josh Allen put aside shouldering the blame of getting his offensive coordinator fired this week by placing an emphasis on injecting a little more energy and joy into his on-field performance.
headlines.shortLinkText: Allen and Bills offense reawaken in 32-6 rout of division rival Jets

events.name: Seattle Seahawks at Los Angeles Rams

headlines.description: — Matthew Stafford left the field hunched in pain after a disastrous flea-flicker ended with Stafford taking a massive hit to the chest while throwing an interception with his Los Angeles Rams already trailing by nine points in the fourth quarter.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rams rally from a late deficit and snap their 3-game skid with a 17-16 win over Seahawks

headlines.description: — Stymied all night by the Minnesota Vikings' smothering defense, Russell Wilson never lost faith in his sputtering offense whose first nine drives ended with Wil Lutz kicking five field goals and Riley Dixon punting four times.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wilson, Sutton hook up for winning TD as Broncos rally to end Vikings' 5-game winning streak, 21-20

events.name: Philadelphia Eagles at Kansas City Chiefs

headlines.description: — The Philadelphia Eagles insisted that their Super Bowl rematch with the Kansas City Chiefs had nothing to do with revenge.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Hurts leads second-half rally as Eagles beat Chiefs 21-17 in Super Bowl rematch
